cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and parsing. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it explores both parametric and non-parametric models for combining parsers. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of more accurate parsers for natural language processing. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as neural networks are used in some of the parsers being combined. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category as some of the techniques used in computer vision, such as ensemble methods, are also used in this paper.
